                            <comment id="96376" author="ys" created="Wed, 15 Oct 2014 07:35:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch landed. Close ticket.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="95902" author="ys" created="Wed, 8 Oct 2014 05:35:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;re-enable test patch: &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/12227&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/12227&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="95397" author="adilger" created="Wed, 1 Oct 2014 07:20:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;sanityn.sh test_21 is still being skipped due to this bug.  In theory the landed patch should have fixed the problem, so this test should be re-enabled.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="53729" author="pjones" created="Mon, 11 Mar 2013 18:27:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Landed for 2.4&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="53167" author="ys" created="Thu, 28 Feb 2013 03:44:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The patch commit to: &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/5556&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/5556&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="53084" author="niu" created="Wed, 27 Feb 2013 02:57:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks the &apos;d21&apos; directory was created in sanity.sh (which was run before sanityn), and it&apos;s not an empty dir, that caused the sanityn test_21 failure. We should just simply improve the sanityn.sh test_21 little bit to remove &apos;d21&apos; directory before testing. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
